BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:02igMf_VakU0ztYVhXDEG
SUMMARY:Youth Clowning with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260301T153242Z
DTSTART:20260302T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Unleash your silly side! A playful\\\, youth-friendly class usi
	ng improv\\\, physical comedy\\\, and clown games to build confidence & cr
	eativity\\n\\n\\n\\nGet ready to unleash your silly side! This series is a
	ll about having fun\\\, taking creative risks\\\, and finding the funny in
	 the unexpected. Working as a group to start\\\, participants will dive he
	ad-over-heels into ensemble theater\\\, improvisation\\\, physical comedy\
	\\, and clown-inspired games\\\, learning how to turn everyday moments int
	o laugh-out-loud comedy. Whether you’re interested in performing or just w
	ant to break out of your comfort zone\\\, this session is all about embrac
	ing play\\\, thinking on your feet\\\, and making bold comedic choices. No
	 experience? No problem! Just bring your imagination\\\, a sense of humor\
	\\, and a willingness to get ridiculous. \\nClass Details\\nDates: 3/2 thr
	u 4/6/26\; Six (6) Monday classes \\nTime: 4:00 pm to 5:20 pm \\nLocation:
	 The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall Stree
	t\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \\nM
	aximum students: 12 \\nAges: 10-15 \\nCost: $320 \\nPrerequisite: None\n\n
	https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/youth-clowning-with-mick-holsb
	eke/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/youth-clowning-with-mick-ho
	lsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\\\, 1315 NW Mall Street
	\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98027
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_qw40t9CqMiJkwytD7_O9
SUMMARY:Clown 100: The Foundations of Clown Play with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260301T153242Z
DTSTART:20260302T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Step into the playful world of Clown! Explore presence\\\, vuln
	erability\\\, and joyful failure through ensemble play and laughter\\n\\n\
	\n\\nWelcome to the world of clowning! This foundational class invites you
	 to step into the playful\\\, unpredictable\\\, and joy-filled realm of Cl
	owning with other folks. Through a series of dynamic exercises in presence
	\\\, play\\\, rhythm\\\, tension\\\, emotional expression\\\, and ensemble
	 play\\\, participants will explore what makes Clown so hilarious and cont
	agious. Embracing vulnerability and the fine art of making mistakes\\\, we
	’ll turn failure into laughter and endless comic gold. Whether you’re new 
	to performance or a seasoned artist\\\, this series will help you build co
	nfidence\\\, take creative risks\\\, and refine your Clown instincts. Come
	 ready to play\\\, surprise yourself\\\, and find the fun in the unexpecte
	d! \\nClass Details\\nDates: Six (6) Monday classes \\nTime: 5:30 pm to 7:
	00 pm \\nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \\n
	1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp
	 Bar & Grill) \\nMaximum students: 16 \\nAges: 18 plus \\nCost: $320 \\nPr
	erequisite: None\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100-
	the-foundations-of-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke/\n\nFrom Unexpected Produ
	ctions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100-the-foundations-o
	f-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\\\, 1315 NW Mall Street
	\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98027
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:-tg5j_rhBpVaEsvi3fw7V
SUMMARY:Theatrical Styles with Alan Hawkins - Issaquah
DTSTAMP:20260301T153242Z
DTSTART:20260303T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Explore bold theatrical styles through improv\\\, from classica
	l and heightened to physical\\\, melodramatic\\\, and contemporary. Come p
	lay.\\n\\n\\n\\nThis class invites improvisers to explore a wide range of 
	theatrical styles and performance traditions\\\, using improvisation as th
	e engine for discovery. While Shakespeare provides one historical foundati
	on\\\, the emphasis is on learning how different styles shape character\\\
	, language\\\, movement\\\, and storytelling—and how to shift between them
	 with confidence and play. \\nThis is a practical\\\, hands-on class focus
	ed on experimentation\\\, adaptability\\\, and joyful risk-taking. \\nWhat
	 You’ll Do\\nExplore a variety of theatrical styles through improvisation\
	\\, including \\n\\nClassical and heightened theatre\\nShakespeare-inspire
	d performance\\nMelodrama and farce\\nPhysical and movement-based theatre\
	\nContemporary and genre-based stage styles\\nLearn how style affects char
	acter\\\, language\\\, physicality\\\, and emotional stakes\\nPractice tra
	nsforming the same scene by changing theatrical style\\nPerform improvised
	 scenes and monologues with clear stylistic choices\\nBuild versatility\\\
	, confidence\\\, and range as a theatrical improviser\\n\\nThis class is i
	deal for students who want to expand their expressive toolbox\\\, deepen t
	heir understanding of theatrical storytelling\\\, and become more adaptabl
	e performers. Whether you’re interested in classical forms\\\, bold physic
	al comedy\\\, modern realism\\\, or stylized stage work\\\, this class off
	ers a playful\\\, supportive space to explore how style shapes the stories
	 we tell. \\nUnexpected Productions Improv School is thrilled to bring our
	 newest Eastside improv classes to Issaquah\\\, serving the communities of
	 the Sammamish Plateau\\\, East Renton\\\, Bellevue\\\, Snoqualmie Valley\
	\\, North Bend\\\, and beyond. \\nClass Details\\nDates: Four (4) Tuesdays
	 \\nTime: 7:00 pm–9:00 pm \\nLocation: Unexpected Productions – Issaquah \
	\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the G
	aslamp Bar and Grill) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: $270 \\nPrerequisit
	e: Improv 100 or equivalent\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event
	/theatrical-styles-with-alan-hawkins-issaquah/\n\nFrom Unexpected Producti
	ons
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/theatrical-styles-with-alan
	-hawkins-issaquah/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
