BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:BPUY42yElNYJIzRpruoJV
SUMMARY:PETS: Southwood Elementary School
DTSTAMP:20260301T153242Z
DTSTART:20260317T201500Z
DESCRIPTION:Written By Melanie Godsey For grades K–5 | 1-hour presentation 
	including performance and actor-led talkback It’s a tail-wagging time at P
	et School\, where Biscuit the pup and all their furry and feathered friend
	s learn to sit\, stay\, and help a human in need. When things get ruff for
	 Biscuit’s best human friend\, Corey\, it’s time to fetch help. A once-clo
	se friendship has gone to the dogs\, and the bus stop becomes a bullying z
	one. Using every paws-itively clever trick from Pet School\, Biscuit will 
	stop at nothing to help Corey and teach the other kids that being an upsta
	nder is the best trick of all. Education Goals: Bullying prevention Turnin
	g bystanders into upstanders Overcoming failure Teamwork\n\nhttps://web.ov
	ationtix.com/trs/pe.c/37019\n\nFrom Taproot Theatre
URL:https://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/37019
LOCATION:Taproot Theatre\, 204 N 85th St\, Seattle\, WA 98103
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:taproot
CATEGORIES:Taproot Theatre
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:KW5Y4AMBCGSnrT04PymG3
SUMMARY:Improv Greenhouse feat: Market Improv
DTSTAMP:20260301T153242Z
DTSTART:20260318T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to be surprised\\\, delighted\\\, and maybe even see 
	your wildest idea take on a life of its own!\\n\\n\\n\\nGraduate Greenhous
	e is a Wednesday night showcase featuring alumni from Unexpected Productio
	ns Improv School. Each performance highlights a different alumni group\\\,
	 putting their training to the test with unpredictable scenes\\\, various 
	formats\\\, and improvised stories. From long-form storytelling to charact
	er work\\\, these performers explore the boundaries of improv. \\nJan 7 Ma
	rket Improv \\nJan 14 \\nJan 21 \\nBut the fun doesn’t stop there! Stick a
	round for a double feature as we roll into Seattle’s longest-running Impro
	v Open Mic: the Duos Open Mic! Starting at 8:00 pm\\\, this weekly showcas
	e promises even more laughs\\\, surprises\\\, and improv magic.\n\nhttps:/
	/www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/graduate-greenhouse-fka-an-improvised
	-holiday-special-2-2/2026-03-18/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/graduate-greenhouse-fka-an-
	improvised-holiday-special-2-2/2026-03-18/
